d Political Allegiance in Early Achaemenid Mesopotamia, and David's career was launched.Weisberg's oeuvre, as exemplified by the nearly three dozen essays conveniently assembled in this volume, attest both to his prodigious industriousness and to the loss that the field of Assyriology has suffered in his untimely demise. As is clear from the Table of Contents, he continued to make major contributions to the study of the Neo-Babylonian period (especially regarding political and military history and the doings of ancient royals) but he also offered seminal insights in other areas, including Masoretic studies, rabbinics, social and economic life of the ancient Near East, as well as the interface between modern culture and study of the ancient world.-Based on W. W. Hallo's "Introduction"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh1 aArnold, Bill T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHallo, William W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLehman, Israel O., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPfeiffer, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeisberg, David B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZion Wacholder, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z978311074526940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781575066882zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781575066882423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781575066882.jpg  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  